The paper deals with graph exploration problems in the context of social networks, which are typically modeled as graphs. The paper also discusses the mixing time and average degree of the graph, which are measures commonly used in the study of random walks on graphs and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). The paper also discusses the use of an oracle to download information about nodes in the graph, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of algorithms in terms of approximation and probability, which is related to machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG).
